# Website deploy workflow

When you change anything under `apps/website/` (HTML, CSS, assets):

1. **Finish the edit** — keep pages static; no build step required.
2. **Commit** the website files (and workflow if touched).
3. **Push to GitHub** on `main` (`origin`) so GitHub Pages deploys via Actions.
4. **Share the live URL** — e.g. https://sach1ng.github.io/tandem/roadmap.html

Do not leave website work local-only. Preview with `npm run roadmap:open` or a local server, but always push when done.

If the user asked not to commit in the same message, finish the edit and remind them the site still needs a push.
